# Core standards

- Make small, safe, incremental changes.
- Read relevant files before editing; avoid blind refactors.
- Keep diffs focused; don’t reformat unrelated code.
- Prefer existing project scripts/tooling (e.g. `package.json`, `Makefile`, `justfile`, `scripts/`).
- Add/adjust tests when behavior changes; run the smallest reasonable checks available.
- Never add secrets (tokens, keys, credentials). Don’t commit `.env`-like files.
